Your queue contains `[1,2,3,4]` at the time of dequeuing. 
```java
        while(!q.isEmpty()){
            current.right = q.remove();
            current.left = null;
            current = current.right;
        }
```
The block never processes `4` as current, since `3` is the last node with a right child. As such, you&#39;re never resetting `4&#39;s` children to `null`, and the right child still points to `3` from the original tree.

This simple check would reset the children for the last node:
```java
        while(!q.isEmpty()){
            current.right = q.remove();
            current.left = null;
            current = current.right;
        }
        current.right = null;
        current.left = null;
````

